Package: clipy
Version: 0.1.0
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Bhavesh Prasad <prasadbhavesh7@gmail.com>
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Depends: python3 (>= 3.10), python3-gi, gir1.2-gtk-4.0, gir1.2-glib-2.0, libglib2.0-bin
Recommends: gnome-shell-extension-appindicator
Suggests: ydotool, python3-xlib
Homepage: https://github.com/Clipy/Clipy
Description: Clipboard history and snippets manager for the system tray
 Clipy for Linux is a faithful clone of the macOS menu-bar app Clipy. It lives
 in the system tray and provides clipboard history (text and images) and
 reusable text snippets, reachable from the tray menu, global hotkeys, and
 searchable pop-up windows.
 .
 Built with GTK4 (PyGObject) and D-Bus. The tray is a hand-rolled
 StatusNotifierItem, so no libappindicator is required. On GNOME Wayland the app
 runs under XWayland so it can monitor the clipboard without keyboard focus.
